oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Skylines, v. 1, no. 3, July 24, 1943
Sky lines; Skyline; Sky line
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: 11th College Training Detachment, Army Air Forces
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Skylines was a publication of the 11th College Training Detachment at MTSC during World War II. This issue has articles about the aviation students; Lieutenant Lawrence Pattock; Navy Air Corps reservists; the reorganization of flights; a pilot who's parachute ripped after he bailed, but he survived; members of the College Training Detachment; and the baseball team
